values: I have an amazing year in 2009. I met Ben DeHaan on (IN) game and we chatted. Hooked up our characters by getting married. His character was a lycan and mine was a vampire. By that time around Sept 2009. We decided to give each other a try irl and so.. He flew me to Wa State, Seattle and we met on his bday on Oct 16, 2009. Stayed there for few days and flew back home then he decided I should move in with him so I flew back there several weeks later and move in with him around after thanksgiving. So... another few months flew by, around Dec 25.. he gave me a hug around 6 in the morning while we were stocking up the socks. He said as he hugged me "I want to grow old with you" then he pulled out a box and inside it was the ring and ask me to marry him and I said "Yes!" So now we've been engaged for over a year and the wedding date is set to July 4, 2011. He put on the 1k gold of diamond in my right hand first cause we both were so freaking tired then I told him "Shouldn't it be in the left hand?" (Lol)... It's so big!.. had to resize it from 5 ro 4 1/2 ring size. XD.. It's been a really long time since I've been here.. I miss you guys. My uncle Mike the one who raised me in from my 8th grade through graduating in May 2004. Is diagnosed with Stage 3 Lung cancer and they said he's got barely 2 weeks to live. It's incurable and the only thing they can help him is ease the pain till he passes away in the Hospital. I prayed alot and kept asking that he would still make it. But it wasn't exactly my prayers but he was asking for me to come to NC, Fayetteville and I'll be flying sometime this weekend there. I've not seen him in over 5 years! I heard he lost alot of weight.. imagine a 57 yr old man, around 6'1-6'3 weighing about 90lbs.. he's so skinny..! And he finally started eating last week, first time in 3 months. O.O That's a good relief that I'll be able to see him before he goes -Starts crying- then I heard today that my friend Truvey had passed away on Jan 11, 2011 at 2:45pm. He had a pneumonia, his heart, lungs and liver were failing. He was fighting it for a while and failed to mention me about it. I've known him for like over 5 years playing (BF) game with him. He always cared about that game and he would put everyone first before him. He was only 47 yrs old. T_T I had an uncle passed away last year before my bday came.. then my grandfather passed away 2 yrs ago half a year before my bday came.. then my great great aunt had died few weeks later of 2007. Now I hear another of my uncle in the Philippines is on 2 oxygen tanks.. It's hard to face the reality of death in your family. I am trying to hold on. Trying to keep it positive that we'll soon all meet them.

His name is Louis Pacini, we've known each other for more than a year now and got together on June 30th. Everything is doing great for me, Louis is going to be here by Sept 18, hopefully if everything goes as his plans.
